### Description
- ruler of the land of the dead
- Not necessarily evil
	- Just the queen of Irkalla
		- Warden of the afterlife
	- But she's tempramental
	- Instance of [[Class - Roots of Hell/Ruler of Hell\|Ruler of Hell]]
- a prisoner there
- [[Unsorted/Common features of Hell#A Ruler\|Common features of Hell#A Ruler]]
- Sometimes referred to as Irkalla
- Sometimes depicted to have a husband/consort
	- Often nonconsentual
	- Typically Nergal, minor god
	- Source story
		- Celebration in surface world
		- Wants party/food
		- Sends someone to retrieve food
			- Emissary badly treated by Nergal
		- Ereshkigal demands Nergal go to Irkalla to apologize
		- Seduces Nergal
		- Nergal wants to go to surface to anounce betrothal
			- Says he'll return, lying
		- Ereshkigal threatens entire surface world
			- "I will send up the dead so that they might devour the living, I will make the dead more numerous than the living"
			- Nergal is forced to return
				- Has to pay guardians this time
		- Ending unknown, presumed kinky
	- Another consort: Dumuzi
		- Originally consort of [[Class - Roots of Hell/Ishtar\|Ishtar]]
			- Has to periodically go to the afterlife to replace [[Class - Roots of Hell/Ishtar\|Ishtar]]
				- Explanation for seasonal changes
				- [[Unsorted/Hell Tropes#Dying vegetation god myths\|Hell Tropes#Dying vegetation god myths]]

### Appearance
- Nude
- Wings and horned crown
- Birdlike talons
	- Related to carrion animals
		- birds/dogs eating dead at dumps and battlefields
